\begin_layout Title
Classical probability measures as pullback of quantum probability measures?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
It is clear that each step of the measurement process is exactly equal or
 just mapped by 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 except we summarize 
\family roman
\size normal
classical measurement process as random variable, but summarize quantum
 measurement process as 
\family default
\size default
observable.
 Notice that after we fix an orthonormal basis
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 is actually an invertible map so that given an observable 
\family roman
\size normal

\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{O}=\sum_{i=0}^{D-1}\lambda_{i}P_{i}$
\end_inset

, we can define an unique random variable 
\family default
\size default

\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{i=0}^{D-1}\lambda_{i}\mathbf{1}_{\varphi^{-1}\left(P_{i}\right)}$
\end_inset

 corresponding to 
\family roman
\size normal

\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{O}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore, we call this random variable as the pullback of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{O}$
\end_inset


\family default
\size default
 by 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

, and denoted by 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi^{*}\mathbf{O}$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
We might also choose the other way around so that each random variable has
 a push forward observable.
 This is better in a sense that we don't have the ambiguity that 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi^{*}\mathbf{O}$
\end_inset

 is might be different for different orthonormal bases, but every theorem
 for IVPMs starts from the quantum part with an observable, so we need the
 notation 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi^{*}\mathbf{O}$
\end_inset

 and fixing an orthonormal basis to disambiguate 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi^{*}\mathbf{O}$
\end_inset

 anyway.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 According to Gleason's theorem, the table could be extended to simplify
 the formula computing expectation values and the the post-measurement-state
 postulates after we define a notation to send probability measures to states
 and the other way around.
\end_layout

